' Run from this directory: plantuml -tsvg diagram.puml

@startuml agent-database-reference-layers
!pragma layout elk
title Agent Database Reference Layers
top to bottom direction

skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam roundcorner 8
skinparam nodesep 35
skinparam ranksep 45
skinparam ArrowColor #53657D
skinparam RectangleBorderColor #53657D
skinparam RectangleBackgroundColor #F7F9FC

' Source evidence:
' - openai/openai-agents-python@2fa463571e76dae8ff267622f1018eaf06ffeb9f,
'   src/agents/memory/sqlite_session.py: SQLiteSession._init_db_for_connection.
' - langchain-ai/langgraph@49ae27c2ae983cfb92091b0dea9f7bc37a716479,
'   libs/checkpoint-postgres/langgraph/checkpoint/postgres/base.py: MIGRATIONS.
' - google/adk-python@be5828f317c7430411df29974cd9ccfa875e90de,
'   src/google/adk/sessions/schemas/v1.py: StorageSession and StorageEvent.
' - microsoft/agent-framework@7c6b1e975f75193ace223a05c6535b8556f93ee4,
'   python/packages/azure-cosmos/agent_framework_azure_cosmos/_checkpoint_storage.py:
'   CosmosCheckpointStorage.
' - letta-ai/letta@b76da9092518cbaa2d09042e52fdcbde69243e18,
'   letta/orm/agent.py: Agent; letta/orm/block.py: Block.
' - Anthropic Managed Agents and AWS AgentCore public documentation accessed 2026-07-20.
' Observed behavior: agent systems persist configuration, runtime events, checkpoints,
' long-term memory, and audit data with different lifecycle and query semantics.
' Design reason: separate data planes prevent conversation logs, execution recovery,
' and cross-session memory from becoming one overloaded messages table.
' Target-only mapping: the layer names below are a comparative model, not a claim that
' every referenced product implements all layers with these exact names.

rectangle "Control Plane\nagent definition and version\nenvironment and policy" as Control #EAF2FF
rectangle "Session Event Plane\nsession and thread\nmessages, tool events, leaf" as Event #E9F7EF
rectangle "Execution Checkpoint Plane\ncheckpoint and parent\nblob and pending writes" as Checkpoint #FFF4E6
rectangle "Long-term Memory Plane\nstore, item, version\nnamespace and embedding" as Memory #F3EEFF
rectangle "Audit And Operation Plane\nidempotency, approval\nretention and deletion" as Audit #FDEEF4

rectangle "OpenAI SDK\nSession + Message" as OpenAI
rectangle "Google ADK\nApp/User/Session + Event" as Google
rectangle "Anthropic / AWS\nManaged event contracts" as Managed
rectangle "LangGraph\nCheckpoint + Store" as LangGraph
rectangle "Microsoft Agent Framework\nCosmos checkpoint document" as Microsoft
rectangle "Letta\nAgent + Conversation + Block + Archive" as Letta

OpenAI --> Event : conversation history
Google --> Event : scoped event log
Managed --> Event : managed events
LangGraph --> Checkpoint : execution recovery
LangGraph --> Memory : cross-thread store
Microsoft --> Checkpoint : full workflow snapshot
Letta --> Control : durable agent
Letta --> Event : conversation messages
Letta --> Memory : blocks and passages

Control -[hidden]right- Event
Event -[hidden]right- Checkpoint
Checkpoint -[hidden]right- Memory
Memory -[hidden]right- Audit

Event --> Audit : append operation and retention
Checkpoint --> Audit : restore and pruning
Memory --> Audit : version and deletion
Control --> Event : resolved configuration
Event --> Checkpoint : recover in-flight work
Event --> Memory : extract durable knowledge

@enduml

@startuml pi-memory-adoption-boundary
!pragma layout smetana
title Pi Memory SR Adoption Boundary
left to right direction

skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam roundcorner 8
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam ArrowColor #53657D

' Source evidence: badlogic/pi-mono@216e672e7c9fc65682553394b74e483c0c9e47f7,
' packages/coding-agent/src/core/session-manager.ts: SessionEntry, _appendEntry,
' buildContextEntries, branch, resetLeaf, and branchWithSummary.
' Observed behavior: pi persists a tree of session entries and rebuilds model context
' from the current leaf path; it does not expose a separate workflow checkpoint store
' or cross-session memory database in this baseline.
' Design reason: the current Memory SR should harden the session event plane without
' presenting future checkpoint and long-term memory tables as current pi behavior.
' Java divergence: durable leaf events, tenant isolation, revisions, and idempotency
' are target-only reliability and security changes.

package "Current SR Scope" #E9F7EF {
  database "agent_session" as Session
  database "session_entry" as Entry
  database "session_leaf_event" as Leaf
  database "session_file_operation" as FileOp
  database "memory_write_operation" as WriteOp
}

package "Separate Future Topics" #F7F9FC {
  rectangle "Agent Control Plane\nagent and version" as AgentControl
  rectangle "Runtime Checkpoint Plane\nrun and checkpoint" as RuntimeCheckpoint
  rectangle "Cross-session Memory Plane\nstore, item, version, embedding" as LongMemory
  rectangle "Artifact Plane\nfile and object metadata" as Artifact
}

Session *--> Entry : owns immutable tree
Session *--> Leaf : materializes leaf changes
Entry *--> FileOp : derived projection
WriteOp --> Session : idempotent command
WriteOp --> Leaf : commits leaf change

AgentControl ..> Session : future resolved snapshot reference
Session ..> RuntimeCheckpoint : future in-flight recovery
Entry ..> LongMemory : future extraction source
Entry ..> Artifact : future content reference

note bottom of Entry
The current source of truth remains
the active session entry path.
end note

note bottom of LongMemory
Not part of SR-MEM-001 v0.4.
Requires independent lifecycle,
retrieval, retention, and deletion design.
end note

@enduml
